What are the limitations of this solution? Are there cases where your service will not work?

    - If the server is stopped, the clients ports will not be closed properly.
    - The server is needed to keep clients alive.
    - Only strings can be sent / received.
    - Strings can be up to 1024 char maximum.
    - An error while connecting to someone exits the program.


Does your system scale? Where is the bottleneck? How many users can it support?

    - Server run on only one thread.
    - Clients are limited to 10 by a variable.

What is the attack surface on the system? How could you reduce it?

    - Clients messages are not checked.

Compatibility: which OS/browsers/systems is our service compatible with?

    - Only compatible with MacOS and Linux based systems.
